In the stipulation itsels‚ as here presented to υς, the following possible claims are compr-ised: those arising from contracts whether stricti iuris or bonae fidei (dare, facere), whether present or future (oportet, oportebit), and whether existing and actionable at once, or existing but not yet actionable (praesens in diemve); those enforce- able by real (petitio) as well as by personal action (actio), whether now (est) or in the future (erit), and by extraordinaria cognitio (persecutio) no less than by ordinary action at law, and whether the promisor has merely detention (habeS, tenes) or has or has had civil possession (possideS, possedisti).
